The paper focuses on developing a search engine for GUI images and metadata extracted from a large corpus of Android apps. This involves techniques from human-computer interaction (cs.HC) to ensure an intuitive user experience, information retrieval (cs.IR) to retrieve relevant screens given a query, software engineering (cs.SE) to develop the search engine, natural language processing (cs.CL) to provide a lightweight query language, and multimedia (cs.MM) to index GUI images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC, followed by cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
